<subSubSection id="C3005997FFA2AA501EA9FC41FEF3FA87" pageId="2" pageNumber="158" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BA50A1CFFA2AA501EA9FC41FEF3FA87" blockId="2.[136,778,805,1838]" pageId="2" pageNumber="158">
<emphasis id="B96ED60EFFA2AA501EA9FC41FE50FC6A" bold="true" box="[189,436,943,970]" pageId="2" pageNumber="158">Emended diagnosis.</emphasis>
Carapace moderate in size; elliptical, oval, circular or subquadrate in outline; umbo anterior or subcentral; growth lines with serrated lower margins; growth bands in umbonal area of the carapace ornamented by long radial lirae that are relatively widely spaced with an intercalated fine reticulation; those on ventral part of carapace ornamented by dense radial lirae that are separated by cross-bars to form chain-like ornament, which appears as radially aligned, discontinuous, short, fine ridges on the external mould (
<bibRefCitation id="EF8B77EDFFA2AA501CFBFB16FEEFFA87" author="Li, G. &amp; Wan, X. Q. &amp; Batten, D. J. &amp; Bengtson, P. &amp; Xi, D. P. &amp; Wang, P. J." pageId="2" pageNumber="158" pagination="687 - 698" refId="ref5213" refString="Li, G., Wan, X. Q., Batten, D. J., Bengtson, P., Xi, D. P. &amp; Wang, P. J. (2009) Spinicaudatans from the Upper Cretaceous Nenjiang Formation of the Songliao Basin, northeast China: taxonomy and biostratigraphy. Cretaceous Research, 30 (3), 687 - 698. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. cretres. 2008.12.008" type="journal article" year="2009">
Li 
<emphasis id="B96ED60EFFA2AA501E9CFAFAFF5DFA87" box="[136,185,1290,1316]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="158">et al</emphasis>
., 2009
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
